{
  "doc_id": "5843",
  "text": "A relative quantitative ELISA, which was previously used by Zhang et al. [CITATION_1] was adopted to detect serum autoantibodies in patients with BC. In brief, a group of IgG gradients, coupled with one blank control, were arranged on the last two columns of wells in duplicate to provide the standard curve. Next, purified recombinant TAAs were tested by ELISA that described in our previous study [CITATION_2] A solution of 3, 3ʹ, 5, 5ʹ-tetramethyl benzidine (TMB)-H 2 O 2 -urea was used as the detecting agent and 50 ul 2M sulfuric acid was added into each well as the stopping solution. The optical density (OD) of each well was read at 450 and 620nm by a Microplate reader (Thermo Fisher Scientific).",
